\begin_layout Enumerate
Explain how Domain Name System (DNS) works by using a domain name: www.netacad.com
 as an example.
 (8 marks) 
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
First, the domain name is entered into the address field of the browser.
 The browser then passes the name, 'www.netacad.com' to a DNS resolver.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
The DNS resolver sends a DNS request containing the address of www.netacad.com
 to a DNS server.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
The servers then searches its record for matching www.netacad.com entries,
 and resolves the name with a corresponding IP address if found.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
If the name is not found, the server passes the request to another server
 to handle the request, this is repeated either until the maximum hops is
 exceeded, or a valid entry is found.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Once a valid entry is found, the DNS server sends the IP address back to
 the resolver, which passes the IP address back to the client that made
 the request.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
The IP address is then used by the client in the encapsulation process as
 the destination address for packets going to www.netacad.com.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
